                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d93">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">463.11 W 891/28: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-05T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 5, 1924—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Department’s telegram number 25, May 31, 1 p.m. I spoke to Foreign Office
                    about this matter on Monday last and received satisfactory assurances. Prochnik
                    has now been authorized by cable to sign tripartite agreement in form already
                    agreed upon without any reservations whatever. His instructions dated 3d instant
                    should now be in Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washburn</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
